# Token Economy

## One task per chat — hard rule
Every distinct task gets its own chat. Never carry a bug investigation into a new feature in the same session. Long chats compound: every turn re-sends the full conversation history.

## NEVER load app.py whole
`app.py` is 31,466 lines (~120k tokens). Loading it whole costs ~$0.50+ per read in Claude Sonnet.

**Always:**
- Grep or SemanticSearch first to find the exact function/route
- Read only the 50–200 line range you need
- Tell the agent the target before it starts: "In `app.py` around `deploy_nodered()` near line ~4200, fix X"

## Cap chat length at ~15 turns
After ~15 back-and-forths, write a HANDOFF note (see `session-handoff.mdc`) and start a fresh chat. Context window compounds — turn 20 costs 4× more than turn 5.

## Use Plan mode to explore, Agent mode to execute
- **Plan mode** (read-only) = cheap exploration, architectural thinking
- **Agent mode** = only when you know exactly what to change

Switching to Plan for "figure out the approach" and back to Agent for "do it" is 2–3x cheaper than doing both in Agent mode.

## Give the agent a line number or function name to anchor on
A vague question = broad search = many file reads = high cost.
- ❌ "Something is broken with Node-RED deploy, find it"
- ✅ "In `deploy_nodered()` around line 4200 of `app.py`, the context backup is not running before stop"
